      "index": 0,
      "text": "copy file \u0027fixture/.build/start.pr\u0027 to \u0027condition-out.txt\u0027, overwrite",
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Drift case 3 \u2014 unary condition operators emitted Right=%!data%, Negate=false\nas placeholders before the per-action notes fix.\n\nStep text \u0060- if %message% is not empty, write out %message%\u0060 uses the unary\n\u0060isnotempty\u0060 operator. With the rule in os/system/modules/condition/if.notes.md\n(\u0022omit Right and Negate when the operator is unary\u0022), the LLM should emit:\nparameters: { Left: %message%, Operator: \u0022isnotempty\u0022 }\nformal:     condition.if(Left=%message%, Operator=\u0022isnotempty\u0022)\n\nPre-fix shape this test forbids: any \u0027Right\u0027 or \u0027Negate\u0027 parameter on\ncondition.if when the operator is unary.\nInspect the \u0060formal\u0060 string \u2014 it mirrors LLM-emitted parameters exactly.\nThe pr also carries a builder-reflected \u0060defaults[]\u0060 array containing\n\u0060negate=false\u0060 for \u0060condition.if\u0060; that\u0027s runtime enrichment, not drift,\nso we don\u0027t assert on the raw pr substring.",
